Dear Directors/Members,

RE- Final reminder to file Beneficial Ownership and Securities Register dec=
larations

Since 24 May 2023, it has been mandatory in terms of the Companies Act (as =
amended) for all companies, external companies and close corporations to fi=
le their Beneficial Ownership/Securities Register information or declaratio=
ns annually with their annual return submission, or as and when it changes.
The Commission urges all non-compliant companies to file their BO informati=
on and not to wait for the filing of the annual returns anniversary period.=
 Newly registered entities must file BO information and securities register=
s within 10 (ten) business days after the date of incorporation.

In August and September 2024, the Commission issued your company an email n=
otification requesting you to file BO information within 7 (seven) business=
 days respectively. If your company has not filed to date, your company is =
non-compliant with the Companies Act, and will be issued with a compliance =
notice upon expiry of the 7 business days referred to above . Once you rece=
ive the compliance notice , you have 15 (fifteen) business days to comply, =
to avoid endorsement of your disclosure certificate where your BO non-compl=
iance will be visible to third parties. Failure to comply may also lead to =
a court sanctioned administrative fine and/or criminal prosecution.

Please ignore this notification if you have already filed your BO informati=
on.

The filing of Beneficial Ownership declarations can be done independently o=
n e-services and non-compliant entities should therefore not wait until the=
ir annual return submissions are due to file the outstanding BO information.

For guidance on how to file the BO declaration, please visit the website fo=
r step-by-step guides: https://urldefense.proofpoint.com/v2/url?u=3Dhttps-3=
A__www.cipc.co.za_-3Fpage-5Fid-3D4447&d=3DDwIFaQ&c=3DeuGZstcaTDllvimEN8b7jX=
rwqOf-v5A_CdpgnVfiiMM&r=3D7ZULBZmD5L4dM8U3nU-5WA&m=3D8F8nbKGfbATRjbQBYtJt6S=
BPCAtSPRA-NjKJIbLp_EIvNbdp6KjbZDbyWA8gtBVC&s=3DnSaYkz4d-Fuc_Nd4M6Ed3LJeXlmk=
qq353Xo3ARwY6iE&e=3D

Kind Regards,

Corporate Compliance and Disclosure Regulation Unit, obo.
Adv RW Voller
Commissioner: CIPC.
NB: In instances where one email address is used for multiple directors, ea=
ch director will receive an individually addressed letter to the same email=
 address.


Please do not reply to this email address for any queries. Contact the CIPC=
 Call Centre at 086 100 2472.





Disclaimer

This message and its attachments is intended for the exclusive use of the n=
amed recipients hereof and may contain information that is privileged or co=
nfidential or otherwise restricted from disclosure wider than the named rec=
ipients. If you are not the named recipient, you are not authorized to read=
, use, transmit, print, retain, copy or disseminate this message or any par=
t thereof, or the attachments thereto. If you have received this message in=
 error, please notify the sender immediately via e-mail and discard (de-ide=
ntify) any paper copies and delete all electronic files of the message.

This email has been scanned for viruses and malware, and may have been auto=
matically archived by Mimecast, a leader in email security and cyber resili=
ence. Mimecast integrates email defenses with brand protection, security aw=
areness training, web security, compliance and other essential capabilities=
. Mimecast helps protect large and small organizations from malicious activ=
ity, human error and technology failure; and to lead the movement toward bu=
ilding a more resilient world. To find out more, visit our website.


